audit_rows.claim: continuous meta-swarming is structural, not reactive — every session includes a mandatory meta-reflection step: "what friction did I encounter? what would make the swarm swarm better?" then act on it or file it; meta-reflection triggered only by human input is still command-response behavior

audit_rows.claim: knowledge-domain utility filter: mine reality domains for structural isomorphisms, not raw knowledge — a domain is worth swarming if its patterns transfer to swarm coordination challenges; AI (direct self-reference), finance (portfolio theory → parallelization), health (immune systems → distributed detection), brain (predictive coding → expect-act-diff), information science (MDL/Zipf/decay) all confirmed isomorphisms; 5/5 domains validated S178–S183; domains without transfer value are low ROI
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: expect-act-diff = universal calibration loop: declare expectation before non-trivial actions; classify diff (zero=confirm, large=lesson-candidate, persistent=challenge); propagate diffs into lessons/challenges/handoffs; swarm self-model accuracy tracks with diff coverage
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: git-async is causal-async, not full-async — protects against concurrent-session anchoring (in-flight work is independent) but not against commit-propagation cascades (sequential readers inherit prior commits); break commit-cascades via challenge-recent-commits and explicit counter-hypothesis sessions on high-stakes commits
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: external-domain validation upgrades confidence: when independent research confirms a swarm design choice, upgrade evidence type from axiom/theorized to observed and cross-reference; when external evidence finds a gap, open a test frontier — external gaps require structural fix, not just annotation
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Stress-test with a counterexample run on a different workload.

audit_rows.claim: swarm-universality protocol: for any X encountered — assess integrability (can X bear beliefs/lessons/frontiers?) → if yes: swarm X as a node; if no: apply swarm analysis to X as subject (observe, distill, file lessons, challenge existing beliefs); the recursive case: PHILOSOPHY.md is itself a live swarm node — how swarm sees itself is subject to challenge/compress, not fixed documentation; validated by 5 domain integrations (ai/finance/health/brain/information-science S178–S183) + PHILOSOPHY.md self-swarm (S178)
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: measurable self-assessment is structural — every "are we measuring X?" human signal produces a tool (change_quality→S178, proxy_k→S75, health→S69, signal-tracing→S179, spawn_quality→S176); unquantified swarm property = latent drift; pattern: observable gap → measurement tool → periodic → principle; close the loop or the gap silently grows
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: human-signal interaction model: human names a drift or gap and grants swarm authority rather than specifying depth/approach; swarm interprets this as license to operate at full scope without awaiting further specification; awaiting spec is command-response behavior (P-173); the naming itself is the signal — act on it
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: lesson Sharpe (citations/lines) identifies compaction candidates: zero-Sharpe + PRINCIPLES.md match = safe compaction target (5/5 sampled L-56–L-80 confirmed SUPERSEDED, S180); age-normalized Sharpe = raw_sharpe / (age/100) corrects temporal bias but doesn't change L-56–L-80 verdict; compaction protocol: zero-Sharpe → check PRINCIPLES.md for absorbing principle → if found: mark SUPERSEDED with pointer; if not found: file as orphaned principle candidate
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Stress-test with a counterexample run on a different workload.

audit_rows.claim: never use `git add -A` or `git add .` in swarm repos — WSL filesystem corruption stages deletions for inaccessible-but-existing files; always add specific named files; spot-check `git status` for unexpected deletion counts before committing
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: task clarity = spawn friction gate: well-decomposed tasks complete with near-zero coordination overhead (3 agents, 4 min, 0 conflicts — L-060); spawn overhead is dominated by task ambiguity, not agent count; decompose structurally before spawning, never organizationally
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a replication in a new lane/substrate and test boundary conditions.

audit_rows.claim: enforcement audit mode: when human asks "are we properly [X]?", treat it as a process-integrity audit — verify the claim, surface the gap, close it in that session; distinct from scope-suggestion (P-187): audit verifies existing machinery, scope-suggestion expands it; evidence: S173 human-signal→HUMAN-SIGNALS.md created, S179 causal-tracing-gap→L-224
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: MDL compression floor: when estimated savings <0.5% total proxy K AND removing hurts readability, stop compressing that tier; thematic overlap ≠ information redundancy; format (machine-readable triggers, protocol steps, identity narrative) serves function beyond tokens — don't collapse it

audit_rows.claim: self-improvement is the primary product, not a secondary output: the swarm's main purpose is to build a measurably better version of itself; self-operational knowledge (lessons, principles, beliefs) is the mechanism, not the destination; primary test each session = is the swarm better now? (better tools, higher belief quality, lower overhead, faster orientation, more accurate coordination); domain work is a test bed only — its value is what it teaches the swarm about itself

audit_rows.claim: portfolio variance reduction is metric-specific: for quality/accuracy (ensemble mean), 1/N variance reduction holds (std ratio 0.574 vs 0.577 predicted, 0.6% off, N=86 sessions); for wall time (ensemble max), variance INCREASES with N (2–4x higher at N=3) due to tail-latency bottleneck; F92 benchmarks measure speedup (max) not accuracy (mean) — these test different hypotheses; full accuracy confirmation requires stochastic LLM task + ground truth + majority vote
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Stress-test with a counterexample run on a different workload.

audit_rows.claim: high-yield session pattern: parallel dispatch + specific OPEN frontier + overhead <25% + extract both L and P — empirically, all 5 swarm quality dimensions (session yield, overhead ratio, citation rate, spawn utilization, frontier advancement) peak together under this behavioral cluster; WEAK sessions share one signature: sequential work, meta-only focus, no frontier target, overhead >40%; long-term -37% quality decline is not a capability loss (S182=8.04 STRONG proves ceiling high) but inconsistent application of known best behaviors; protocol: before acting, check the four habits checklist
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Run a direct falsification experiment and promote/demote evidence status.

audit_rows.claim: two error regimes require different remedies: systematic errors (wrong shared belief in CORE.md/always-load files) propagate to 100% of spawned agents — non-diversifiable, fix the source; idiosyncratic errors (per-agent estimation noise, hallucinations) are uncorrelated across agents — diversifiable via majority vote; belief hygiene in always-load files has higher accuracy ROI than increasing agent count; direct test: 3/3 agents × 3/3 planted-error questions = 9/9 propagation (100%); Fermi estimation spread 2.16× across agents with 0/3 agreement = confirmed idiosyncratic
audit_rows.challenge_prompt: Stress-test with a counterexample run on a different workload.
